1
00:00:36,286 --> 00:00:37,579
Come on, spill it.

2
00:00:37,662 --> 00:00:40,749
A government agency activated
Code Red for CHENES.

3
00:00:42,292 --> 00:00:43,376
They are in Hong Kong?

4
00:00:43,460 --> 00:00:45,003
They found us.

5
00:00:45,086 --> 00:00:48,882
But the question remains,
who helped them escape?

6
00:00:48,965 --> 00:00:51,009
<i>I know a way</i>

7
00:00:51,092 --> 00:00:53,470
<i>for them to escape to Hong Kong.</i>

8
00:00:53,553 --> 00:00:56,431
But you know what that means.

9
00:00:56,514 --> 00:00:59,893
Mikoy will be branded
a traitor to the agency.

10
00:00:59,976 --> 00:01:01,269
<i>And you'll hunt him down.</i>

11
00:01:04,230 --> 00:01:06,733
I guess I must fix this myself.

12
00:01:06,816 --> 00:01:08,026
<i>Let's begin.</i>

13
00:01:08,902 --> 00:01:10,028
Chiara!

14
00:01:10,945 --> 00:01:12,697
Giancarlo de Luca?

15
00:01:13,281 --> 00:01:15,742
His name is Donatello Belladonna.

16
00:01:15,825 --> 00:01:17,202
The Painter.

17
00:01:17,285 --> 00:01:18,453
Let me handle this first, Chiara.

18
00:01:18,536 --> 00:01:20,163
Let me take down Giancarlo.

19
00:01:20,246 --> 00:01:22,832
I've already been trained
by Agent Alex at the agency.

20
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:23,625
Who?

21
00:01:29,547 --> 00:01:31,049
Because in a real fight,

22
00:01:31,132 --> 00:01:33,843
every part of the body is fair game.

23
00:01:37,388 --> 00:01:38,681
Mikoy!

24
00:01:38,765 --> 00:01:40,141
Sorry.

25
00:01:42,310 --> 00:01:43,269
Stop!

26
00:02:03,540 --> 00:02:04,582
Take my hand.

27
00:02:08,545 --> 00:02:09,546
My arm's getting tired.

28
00:02:10,713 --> 00:02:11,923
Of course not!

29
00:02:12,006 --> 00:02:13,091
I don't trust you.

30
00:02:13,174 --> 00:02:15,844
You might double-cross me.

31
00:02:21,850 --> 00:02:22,976
Wow!

32
00:02:23,059 --> 00:02:24,018
Chiara?

33
00:02:25,019 --> 00:02:27,564
What's this? First-name basis? Why?

34
00:02:27,647 --> 00:02:29,607
Are you close to my sweetheart?

35
00:02:29,691 --> 00:02:30,650
Huh?

36
00:02:35,822 --> 00:02:36,865
Chiara,

37
00:02:36,948 --> 00:02:38,950
you found someone who's skilled in combat

38
00:02:39,033 --> 00:02:41,786
and apparently skilled in romance too.

39
00:02:50,753 --> 00:02:51,671
Or

40
00:02:52,547 --> 00:02:56,050
perhaps he was forged by the strength
of your love for each other.

41
00:02:57,176 --> 00:02:58,219
First of all,

42
00:02:58,303 --> 00:02:59,512
I wasn't forged.

43
00:02:59,596 --> 00:03:00,847
I'm Pinagpala.

44
00:03:00,930 --> 00:03:02,515
And can you please move over there?

45
00:03:02,599 --> 00:03:03,933
Back away from me.

46
00:03:04,517 --> 00:03:06,561
Why are you even here?
Why are you so close?

47
00:03:06,644 --> 00:03:07,520
Easy.

48
00:03:07,604 --> 00:03:09,522
- Give us space!
- All right.

49
00:03:10,648 --> 00:03:12,275
Easy there, mister.

50
00:03:12,358 --> 00:03:13,943
As if we don't have history together.

51
00:03:14,027 --> 00:03:15,570
We don't!

52
00:03:15,653 --> 00:03:16,571
Are you high?

53
00:03:17,155 --> 00:03:19,616
And seriously, you're our enemy.

54
00:03:19,699 --> 00:03:21,701
So stop acting all buddy-buddy.

55
00:03:31,836 --> 00:03:33,046
Right?

56
00:03:38,426 --> 00:03:39,427
Ow!

57
00:03:46,184 --> 00:03:48,478
What? Was I supposed to thank you?

58
00:03:51,522 --> 00:03:52,565
I just had this done.

59
00:03:55,235 --> 00:03:58,154
I want constant updates on her location.

60
00:03:58,238 --> 00:03:59,197
Okay?

61
00:04:01,783 --> 00:04:03,826
By the way, why didn't you go with her?

62
00:04:05,119 --> 00:04:06,329
We're out of budget.

63
00:04:07,997 --> 00:04:10,959
Or maybe you're just afraid
of getting jealous

64
00:04:11,042 --> 00:04:16,589
when you see Agent Alex reunite
with her most beloved asset.

65
00:04:16,673 --> 00:04:18,049
That's not true.

66
00:04:18,132 --> 00:04:20,176
It's better that she
went there on her own.

67
00:04:20,969 --> 00:04:21,970
Alone.

68
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:23,721
Really?

69
00:04:24,305 --> 00:04:26,975
And my passport already expired.
I haven't renewed it yet.

70
00:04:28,226 --> 00:04:29,686
There, you admitted it.

71
00:04:29,769 --> 00:04:31,729
You wanted to go.

72
00:04:35,358 --> 00:04:38,528
What if Agent Alex
manages to bring Mikoy back?

73
00:04:38,611 --> 00:04:39,696
That's not happening.

74
00:04:39,779 --> 00:04:40,780
Why not?

75
00:04:40,863 --> 00:04:43,908
Because that fool is hopelessly in love.

76
00:04:43,992 --> 00:04:47,203
I mean, he's head over heels
for Chiara Valtrovi.

77
00:04:47,287 --> 00:04:51,207
And once you reach that level
of foolishness,

78
00:04:52,166 --> 00:04:53,584
it's hard to come back from it.

79
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:56,713
I don't think Mikoy is planning
to come back to us soon.

80
00:05:04,053 --> 00:05:05,096
Fool.

81
00:05:13,938 --> 00:05:14,939
Are you okay?

82
00:05:15,565 --> 00:05:16,941
I'm fine.

83
00:05:17,025 --> 00:05:18,484
There's nothing to worry about.

84
00:05:18,568 --> 00:05:20,445
It's just like an ant bite.

85
00:05:21,029 --> 00:05:22,697
An ant bite?

86
00:05:22,780 --> 00:05:24,240
More like a dinosaur bite.

87
00:05:25,783 --> 00:05:26,951
All right.

88
00:05:27,035 --> 00:05:28,911
This place should be secure.

89
00:05:28,995 --> 00:05:31,289
It's a safehouse owned
by a friend from the Triad.

90
00:05:32,457 --> 00:05:33,916
I thought it was safe.

91
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,251
Then why did you lock the door?

92
00:05:40,506 --> 00:05:41,716
Fair enough.

93
00:05:41,799 --> 00:05:45,720
Even antibacterial soap
kills only 99.9% of bacteria.

94
00:05:45,803 --> 00:05:47,555
There's still that remaining 0.1%.

95
00:05:47,638 --> 00:05:48,514
So you know what? You're right.

96
00:05:48,598 --> 00:05:50,391
It's better to be safe than sorry.

97
00:05:50,475 --> 00:05:52,643
Wow. You're something else, Mikoy.

98
00:05:52,727 --> 00:05:54,896
You compared our situation to bacteria?

99
00:05:56,689 --> 00:05:59,901
You said this place is protected
by the Triad, right?

100
00:06:00,943 --> 00:06:02,695
Is that where you got the gun?

101
00:06:03,279 --> 00:06:06,783
Yes, that's the only logical reason
how I got the firearm.

102
00:06:07,408 --> 00:06:08,576
But why?

103
00:06:08,659 --> 00:06:10,870
The Triad isn't a friend of the Concordat.

104
00:06:10,953 --> 00:06:11,996
Well.

105
00:06:12,830 --> 00:06:16,292
Chiara, you know I can be extremely
persuasive sometimes.

106
00:06:16,876 --> 00:06:19,378
Wait, wait, hold on. I don't get it.

107
00:06:19,462 --> 00:06:20,797
Why are you helping us?

108
00:06:21,506 --> 00:06:23,591
Weren't you sent by that
La Morte Bianca thing

109
00:06:23,674 --> 00:06:25,635
to kill Chiara and me?

110
00:06:25,718 --> 00:06:27,136
Yes, that's correct.

111
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:29,013
I was sent here by La Morte Bianca.

112
00:06:29,597 --> 00:06:31,557
But not to kill this little one.

113
00:06:32,892 --> 00:06:34,352
Little one?

114
00:06:35,645 --> 00:06:37,688
What happened? Are you okay?

115
00:06:38,648 --> 00:06:40,650
I just got injured
during training earlier.

116
00:06:40,733 --> 00:06:41,609
But I'm okay.

117
00:06:41,692 --> 00:06:43,111
You don't look okay.

118
00:06:43,194 --> 00:06:45,530
I told you to always be careful.

119
00:06:46,114 --> 00:06:48,116
I'm the one who got hurt,

120
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:49,283
yet you're scolding me.

121
00:06:49,367 --> 00:06:51,160
You're actually talking back?

122
00:06:51,244 --> 00:06:52,245
I'm just worried.

123
00:06:52,328 --> 00:06:53,496
Wow.

124
00:06:53,579 --> 00:06:54,831
Your Tagalog is getting better.

125
00:06:59,585 --> 00:07:01,420
Enough about me. Who did this to you?

126
00:07:04,715 --> 00:07:05,758
Big Joe?

127
00:07:07,385 --> 00:07:09,720
- He's big, but that's all.
- What should I do?

128
00:07:23,943 --> 00:07:25,403
You're so stubborn!

129
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:40,460
But can I still trust you?

130
00:07:41,043 --> 00:07:42,086
Chiara.

131
00:07:49,886 --> 00:07:52,889
Well, I was wondering why
La Morte Bianca sent you.

132
00:07:57,768 --> 00:07:59,896
Or maybe she actually wants to know

133
00:07:59,979 --> 00:08:02,732
if I can actually kill this ugly person.

134
00:08:02,815 --> 00:08:04,859
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey! Foul!

135
00:08:04,942 --> 00:08:06,277
This face is movie-star material.

136
00:08:23,127 --> 00:08:24,170
And she'll kill you?

137
00:08:26,214 --> 00:08:28,132
Because before she even finds out,

138
00:08:28,216 --> 00:08:30,676
I may be far, far away
in Davao or Mindanao

139
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:33,012
or maybe in… South Africa.

140
00:08:33,095 --> 00:08:34,472
Doing the tango or salsa.

141
00:08:38,684 --> 00:08:40,269
At least you have a Plan B.

142
00:08:40,353 --> 00:08:41,312
Yes.

143
00:08:41,395 --> 00:08:43,731
Because I don't intend to kill

144
00:08:43,814 --> 00:08:45,399
your stupid boyfriend here.

145
00:08:50,404 --> 00:08:51,739
Exactly!

146
00:08:51,822 --> 00:08:52,865
What's with all the "stupid"?

147
00:08:58,913 --> 00:09:00,998
Okay, now you're going too far.

148
00:09:13,177 --> 00:09:14,679
You know, you've been at it
for a while now.

149
00:09:14,762 --> 00:09:16,764
You've been taking shots at me
this whole time.

150
00:09:17,348 --> 00:09:19,267
For your information, I'm not ugly.

151
00:09:19,850 --> 00:09:22,186
They say I look like Enrique Gil.

152
00:09:22,270 --> 00:09:23,813
If you're Enrique Gil,

153
00:09:23,896 --> 00:09:24,981
then I'm Brad Pitt.

154
00:09:25,064 --> 00:09:27,275
- Impossible, right?
- Woah!

155
00:09:27,358 --> 00:09:28,276
- Brad Pitt, really?
- Yes!

156
00:09:28,359 --> 00:09:29,277
If you're Enrique Gil,

157
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:30,570
- you're…
- You're…

158
00:09:30,653 --> 00:09:31,612
- You're…
- You're…

159
00:09:31,696 --> 00:09:32,989
Stop!

160
00:09:33,072 --> 00:09:34,991
Both of you, please!

161
00:09:35,950 --> 00:09:38,077
And you, I know you.

162
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:40,830
Why do you keep saying ugly things?

163
00:09:40,913 --> 00:09:43,082
You only say that
when you know something is up.

164
00:09:43,666 --> 00:09:45,459
Chiara? Mikoy?

165
00:09:51,966 --> 00:09:56,012
<i>You and Mikoy still haven't seen</i>
<i>what La Morte Bianca</i>

166
00:09:56,095 --> 00:09:57,680
<i>is capable of doing.</i>

167
00:10:54,945 --> 00:10:56,906
But we need to go now. Let's go.

168
00:10:56,989 --> 00:10:58,115
Chiara?

169
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:03,204
Don't ignore what I told you
about La Morte Bianca.

170
00:11:04,789 --> 00:11:06,624
I'm not ignoring it.

171
00:11:10,044 --> 00:11:13,339
I know she's really dangerous,

172
00:11:13,422 --> 00:11:14,715
but I'm also dangerous,

173
00:11:14,799 --> 00:11:16,842
and I know Mikoy and I can handle this.

174
00:11:17,426 --> 00:11:18,719
Right, sweetheart?

175
00:11:20,596 --> 00:11:21,680
But seriously,

176
00:11:22,390 --> 00:11:25,309
thank you for the warning.
I really appreciate it.

177
00:11:25,393 --> 00:11:26,602
Do you have an exit plan?

178
00:11:32,149 --> 00:11:33,901
Stop. I'll do it.

179
00:11:33,984 --> 00:11:35,611
Give that to me.

180
00:11:35,694 --> 00:11:36,737
Just move over there.

181
00:11:36,821 --> 00:11:37,696
What are you doing?

182
00:11:37,780 --> 00:11:39,407
I'm fine. I can do it.

183
00:11:39,490 --> 00:11:41,242
You're clearly struggling to carry that!

184
00:11:41,951 --> 00:11:45,162
Okay! Sorry! Sorry, sir! Sorry, sir.

185
00:11:47,498 --> 00:11:48,582
Are these for delivery?

186
00:11:48,666 --> 00:11:51,419
I'll just put these at the stall,
so they can see them right away.

187
00:11:52,503 --> 00:11:53,379
I'll do it!

188
00:11:54,630 --> 00:11:56,090
Why are you so sweet?

189
00:11:57,133 --> 00:11:58,759
You don't want me to get tired, huh?

190
00:11:58,843 --> 00:12:00,010
In your dreams!

191
00:12:00,094 --> 00:12:02,721
I just want to finish this quickly,
so you can go home.

192
00:12:05,349 --> 00:12:07,309
You want me to go home right away?

193
00:12:08,686 --> 00:12:09,603
What a waste!

194
00:12:09,687 --> 00:12:12,815
I still have a valuable update
about your brother.

195
00:12:13,357 --> 00:12:14,733
Someone might hear you.

196
00:12:15,526 --> 00:12:16,527
Lower your voice.

197
00:12:17,194 --> 00:12:18,612
Relax!

198
00:12:18,696 --> 00:12:21,073
Earlier, you wanted me gone, now…

199
00:12:21,157 --> 00:12:22,491
you're holding me?

200
00:12:22,575 --> 00:12:23,659
You, huh.

201
00:12:24,243 --> 00:12:25,202
No!

202
00:12:26,871 --> 00:12:27,913
Go home already!

203
00:12:28,664 --> 00:12:31,834
Mom and Dad are coming back.
The store is close by.

204
00:12:32,334 --> 00:12:33,627
Okay!

205
00:12:33,711 --> 00:12:35,671
I get it! You don't need help!

206
00:12:35,754 --> 00:12:36,964
But…

207
00:12:37,047 --> 00:12:40,092
don't you really want to know
the update about your brother?

208
00:12:42,803 --> 00:12:43,846
Okay.

209
00:12:43,929 --> 00:12:46,140
Silence means yes.

210
00:12:46,223 --> 00:12:48,517
All right. I'll just go home.

211
00:12:49,018 --> 00:12:50,769
Okay! Okay! Okay!

212
00:12:51,437 --> 00:12:52,396
You're winning.

213
00:12:54,482 --> 00:12:56,567
Tell me the update about Mikoy.

214
00:12:57,193 --> 00:12:58,194
Here goes.

215
00:12:59,862 --> 00:13:02,907
Look at our boy there.

216
00:13:02,990 --> 00:13:05,201
I've never seen him like that before.

217
00:13:06,452 --> 00:13:09,705
Look. Look at those moves.

218
00:13:09,788 --> 00:13:13,876
The way he's pressing his lips
to Sofie's ear, right?

219
00:13:13,959 --> 00:13:15,252
Like…

220
00:13:15,336 --> 00:13:17,963
Just like us when we were younger.

221
00:13:18,047 --> 00:13:20,216
You only liked me
because I'm sweet, right?

222
00:13:20,299 --> 00:13:22,009
You're always fooling around!

223
00:13:22,092 --> 00:13:23,010
Come on.

224
00:13:26,347 --> 00:13:27,389
Wait a second.

225
00:13:27,890 --> 00:13:29,600
Why would I tell you?

226
00:13:47,576 --> 00:13:50,538
It's okay. I still have a spare.

227
00:13:51,288 --> 00:13:53,457
What are you talking about? What spare?

228
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:55,084
Nothing.

229
00:13:55,167 --> 00:13:56,043
Here.

230
00:13:56,126 --> 00:13:59,129
What do you call a man who has no balls
even if he has a spare?

231
00:13:59,838 --> 00:14:01,715
- What?
- Mikoy!

232
00:14:03,759 --> 00:14:05,302
- Mikoy!
- Okay, okay, okay.

233
00:14:05,386 --> 00:14:06,595
You two are having fun, huh?

234
00:14:06,679 --> 00:14:08,847
I wish we could stay longer
so you could bond some more,

235
00:14:08,931 --> 00:14:11,183
but we don't have any time left.

236
00:14:12,810 --> 00:14:14,436
Hey, dear.

237
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:17,106
You're still here.

238
00:14:17,189 --> 00:14:21,026
So you really committed
to your stop-for-the-day plan, huh?

239
00:14:21,110 --> 00:14:22,278
Of course, Auntie.

240
00:14:22,361 --> 00:14:24,780
You know, it's so boring at the resort,

241
00:14:24,864 --> 00:14:28,367
so I just stayed here
to spend time with Angelito.

242
00:14:28,450 --> 00:14:30,244
Wait a minute.

243
00:14:30,327 --> 00:14:31,662
Don't you have company?

244
00:14:31,745 --> 00:14:34,582
What's the trend these days in your town?

245
00:14:34,665 --> 00:14:36,292
Is this solo travel?

246
00:14:36,375 --> 00:14:38,502
Oh, no, Auntie. I have company.

247
00:14:38,586 --> 00:14:40,379
Actually, he's on his way here.

248
00:14:40,462 --> 00:14:43,007
He said he'll text me when he arrives.

249
00:14:46,468 --> 00:14:47,595
Speaking of!

250
00:14:49,638 --> 00:14:50,472
Dad, sir!

251
00:14:53,142 --> 00:14:54,351
Hey.

252
00:15:03,027 --> 00:15:05,362
I'll see you again, Giancarlo De Luca.

253
00:15:05,446 --> 00:15:07,364
Don't call me that! My name is Donatello!

254
00:15:07,448 --> 00:15:08,866
Oh, Donatello!

255
00:15:08,949 --> 00:15:11,243
All right, say hi
to Master Splinter for me,

256
00:15:11,327 --> 00:15:14,413
and Raphael, Leonardo, and Michelangelo.

257
00:15:14,496 --> 00:15:17,082
Okay, happy now
with your Ninja Turtle jokes?

258
00:15:17,666 --> 00:15:18,959
- I'm happy for you. Happy for you, boy.
- Kind of.

259
00:15:21,170 --> 00:15:22,087
Okay, okay.

260
00:15:22,171 --> 00:15:23,047
- Let's go!
- Okay.

261
00:15:23,631 --> 00:15:24,882
Don't move!

262
00:15:24,965 --> 00:15:26,133
Put your hands up!

263
00:15:26,884 --> 00:15:28,010
Agent Alex.

264
00:15:28,552 --> 00:15:29,428
I missed you.

265
00:15:29,511 --> 00:15:31,096
I said, hands up.

266
00:15:31,180 --> 00:15:32,640
- All of you!
- Okay!

267
00:15:32,723 --> 00:15:33,599
Here we go!

268
00:15:34,183 --> 00:15:35,726
And don't try to do anything stupid,

269
00:15:35,809 --> 00:15:37,895
because I won't hesitate
to pull the trigger.

270
00:15:55,204 --> 00:15:58,540
Good afternoon, Mario, Tess.

271
00:16:00,501 --> 00:16:04,088
Thank you for letting Sofie
stay here for a while.

272
00:16:06,632 --> 00:16:07,883
Wait.

273
00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:10,135
You look very familiar.

274
00:16:10,761 --> 00:16:12,388
So familiar.

275
00:16:12,471 --> 00:16:14,974
Maybe because you look like your cake

276
00:16:15,557 --> 00:16:16,558
when it's burnt.

277
00:16:17,309 --> 00:16:19,728
No! Wait a minute!

278
00:16:21,981 --> 00:16:23,399
Oh my!

279
00:16:24,274 --> 00:16:26,276
Bertong Butete!

280
00:16:29,571 --> 00:16:30,906
Who's Butete?

281
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:32,741
Your father.

282
00:16:33,367 --> 00:16:34,660
He looks like a tadpole.

283
00:16:35,494 --> 00:16:37,663
Oh, Mario!

284
00:16:37,746 --> 00:16:38,622
You know,

285
00:16:38,706 --> 00:16:40,749
don't pay too much attention
to my husband.

286
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:42,084
He's a joker!

287
00:16:49,675 --> 00:16:50,551
Surprised?

288
00:16:50,634 --> 00:16:52,177
I know the language

289
00:16:52,261 --> 00:16:54,430
because Italian was my elective
in college.

290
00:16:55,389 --> 00:16:57,766
I've also read <i>Inferno</i>, <i>Purgatorio</i>,

291
00:16:57,850 --> 00:16:58,809
and <i>Paradiso</i>,

292
00:16:59,476 --> 00:17:01,812
by Dante Alighieri, for my thesis work.

293
00:17:01,895 --> 00:17:03,397
Excellent! You know <i>Divine Comedy</i>.

294
00:17:04,440 --> 00:17:05,899
Funny, isn't it?

295
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:07,901
Even though it's called <i>Divine Comedy</i>,

296
00:17:07,985 --> 00:17:09,278
it's not actually funny.

297
00:17:10,487 --> 00:17:13,240
Are we done reminiscing
about our literature courses?

298
00:17:13,866 --> 00:17:16,827
Come on. It's like
I'm the third wheel here.

299
00:17:16,910 --> 00:17:18,078
- Aren't we friends?
- Back off!

300
00:17:20,289 --> 00:17:21,999
It's been a long time since we last met.

301
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:26,754
Get Sofie inside the house.
It's hot outside.

302
00:17:26,837 --> 00:17:28,297
Sofie, come with me!

303
00:17:33,719 --> 00:17:35,137
You two.

304
00:17:35,721 --> 00:17:37,723
You better be sitting with each other.

305
00:17:37,806 --> 00:17:40,768
We'll have a peaceful meal later.

306
00:17:41,602 --> 00:17:42,561
Okay?

307
00:17:43,145 --> 00:17:45,564
Talk to your husband.

308
00:17:46,065 --> 00:17:47,232
He started it.

309
00:17:48,650 --> 00:17:50,277
He looks like Minecraft Steve anyway.

310
00:17:51,612 --> 00:17:52,946
See? He started again.

311
00:17:53,030 --> 00:17:54,531
These two are at it again.

312
00:17:54,615 --> 00:17:56,700
Follow me. Come on!

313
00:17:57,868 --> 00:18:00,287
You look like Steve Martin.

314
00:18:00,370 --> 00:18:01,246
<i>Friends?</i>

315
00:18:03,082 --> 00:18:04,708
We're not friends, Mikoy.

316
00:18:06,835 --> 00:18:09,046
Because a real friend

317
00:18:09,129 --> 00:18:11,131
doesn't disappear without a word.

318
00:18:12,508 --> 00:18:13,926
A real friend

319
00:18:14,510 --> 00:18:15,928
doesn't leave you hanging.

320
00:18:17,429 --> 00:18:18,347
That sounded personal.

321
00:18:19,306 --> 00:18:20,265
Wow!

322
00:18:26,230 --> 00:18:27,147
How about--

323
00:18:27,231 --> 00:18:29,608
My God! Agent Sianong!

324
00:18:29,691 --> 00:18:33,112
If you just wanted updates
about Agent Alex,

325
00:18:33,195 --> 00:18:35,072
you should've teleported to Hong Kong.

326
00:18:35,697 --> 00:18:36,865
That's harsh.

327
00:18:37,407 --> 00:18:39,118
You're so grumpy.

328
00:18:39,201 --> 00:18:41,703
I just wanted to know
if there's any update on Alex.

329
00:18:42,287 --> 00:18:43,956
Maybe we can talk about this?

330
00:18:44,039 --> 00:18:45,707
I'll explain everything.

331
00:18:46,583 --> 00:18:48,210
Mikoy, you'd better do that.

332
00:18:48,794 --> 00:18:50,671
Shut up!

333
00:18:50,754 --> 00:18:52,422
Or I'll have you shot.

334
00:18:53,465 --> 00:18:54,716
I'm sorry.

335
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:56,969
I mean, you're the girlfriend,

336
00:18:57,052 --> 00:18:59,471
and she is the…

337
00:18:59,555 --> 00:19:02,516
ex-girlfriend, correct?

338
00:19:03,016 --> 00:19:04,643
What exactly are you going to explain?

339
00:19:05,811 --> 00:19:08,063
That this is for the greater good
of the agency?

340
00:19:08,147 --> 00:19:09,606
For our countrymen?

341
00:19:11,608 --> 00:19:13,068
Mikoy, you ran away.

342
00:19:13,652 --> 00:19:15,279
And you betrayed the cause.

343
00:19:17,531 --> 00:19:19,449
You can't do anything here.

344
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:21,326
You have no jurisdiction here,

345
00:19:21,410 --> 00:19:24,204
so why don't you just let us leave

346
00:19:24,288 --> 00:19:26,874
because my arms are getting tired.

347
00:19:28,750 --> 00:19:30,002
You are a Moraviano.

348
00:19:31,378 --> 00:19:34,006
And Mikoy has an ex parte
warrant of arrest.

349
00:19:34,089 --> 00:19:37,718
And I can shoot all of you
right here if I want to.

350
00:19:39,970 --> 00:19:42,848
And this guy right here,
who looks like Giancarlo,

351
00:19:43,348 --> 00:19:44,558
he's evil to the core.

352
00:19:45,434 --> 00:19:47,978
So I'm doing the world a favor
by eliminating him.

353
00:19:48,979 --> 00:19:50,480
And if you think about it,

354
00:19:50,564 --> 00:19:52,399
the world will be a better place

355
00:19:53,108 --> 00:19:54,443
without all of you.

356
00:20:02,242 --> 00:20:06,163
What if Alex
is already sending you a distress call,

357
00:20:06,246 --> 00:20:07,706
but because you're so busy

358
00:20:07,789 --> 00:20:09,791
with your laptop and four phones,

359
00:20:09,875 --> 00:20:11,460
you don't even notice it?

360
00:20:11,543 --> 00:20:12,628
Because that's how it goes, right?

361
00:20:12,711 --> 00:20:15,547
That's how it is in movies and TV dramas.

362
00:20:15,631 --> 00:20:17,174
When the hero is in danger,

363
00:20:17,257 --> 00:20:20,093
they call their contact person, right?

364
00:20:20,177 --> 00:20:21,428
But then that contact person

365
00:20:21,511 --> 00:20:23,513
gets interrupted by another call
or conversation.

366
00:20:23,597 --> 00:20:25,641
Or something suddenly falls.

367
00:20:25,724 --> 00:20:28,143
Or their phone is on silent.

368
00:20:28,227 --> 00:20:29,978
Or the battery is dead.

369
00:20:31,230 --> 00:20:32,272
Dara,

370
00:20:32,981 --> 00:20:35,359
I just want to make sure Alex is safe.

371
00:20:35,442 --> 00:20:36,360
That's all.

372
00:20:38,070 --> 00:20:39,196
Point taken.

373
00:20:39,905 --> 00:20:41,823
But this isn't a movie.

374
00:20:41,907 --> 00:20:43,283
It was just an example.

375
00:20:44,493 --> 00:20:46,495
I understand why you're worried about her,

376
00:20:46,578 --> 00:20:48,580
because of your

377
00:20:49,331 --> 00:20:51,959
one-sided feelings for her.

378
00:21:01,510 --> 00:21:03,428
Wow, you're really pushing
the one-sided thing.

379
00:21:04,137 --> 00:21:05,180
Okay.

380
00:21:06,306 --> 00:21:07,683
Then do it.

381
00:21:08,934 --> 00:21:09,810
Shoot us.

382
00:21:09,893 --> 00:21:10,727
Sweetheart.

383
00:21:11,353 --> 00:21:12,562
What are you waiting for?

384
00:21:13,188 --> 00:21:14,147
Come on.

385
00:21:14,731 --> 00:21:18,277
Shoot us from that moral
high ground you're standing on.

386
00:21:24,241 --> 00:21:26,785
I thought I had your back
when it comes to Alex?

387
00:21:26,868 --> 00:21:27,995
Yes.

388
00:21:28,620 --> 00:21:30,455
I'm Team SiaLex

389
00:21:30,956 --> 00:21:32,958
or Asiong.

390
00:21:33,542 --> 00:21:35,836
My point is,

391
00:21:35,919 --> 00:21:38,088
Agent Alex is a grown woman.

392
00:21:39,881 --> 00:21:42,342
And if she needs our help,

393
00:21:42,426 --> 00:21:44,678
she will definitely call us.

394
00:21:47,472 --> 00:21:49,099
Please, please. Time out first.

395
00:21:49,683 --> 00:21:50,517
Can we?

396
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:52,311
Let's all relax for a moment.

397
00:21:53,020 --> 00:21:53,979
Okay?

398
00:21:54,730 --> 00:21:56,940
Chiara, sweetheart, I'm sorry, but please.

399
00:21:57,024 --> 00:21:58,400
Don't say anything yet, okay?

400
00:21:58,483 --> 00:22:01,653
Let me do the explaining first, okay?

401
00:22:01,737 --> 00:22:03,905
Alex, believe me.

402
00:22:03,989 --> 00:22:06,533
I didn't betray the agency, okay?

403
00:22:06,616 --> 00:22:07,617
And Chiara

404
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:09,244
is no longer with the Moravianos.

405
00:22:10,662 --> 00:22:11,913
Then what is she?

406
00:22:23,592 --> 00:22:24,718
Something like that.

407
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:29,848
Why?

408
00:22:29,931 --> 00:22:32,976
Do you think I would lie to you?

409
00:22:58,001 --> 00:22:59,127
Stay there.

410
00:23:07,636 --> 00:23:09,054
Don't you want to fight fairly?

411
00:23:10,639 --> 00:23:11,932
I don't have the gun.

412
00:23:19,231 --> 00:23:20,607
Gosh, the electricity is gone.

413
00:23:20,690 --> 00:23:22,901
Don't worry. The generator will work soon.

414
00:23:25,278 --> 00:23:26,279
See. Thank you.

415
00:23:30,450 --> 00:23:31,535
Sorry.

416
00:23:32,994 --> 00:23:34,538
Alex! What are you doing?

417
00:23:35,539 --> 00:23:36,790
Chiara? Chiara…
